Säure Adler.title: Kwasarstunde
Säure Adler.about:
Emerging from the cosmic depths of Poland, Kwasarstunde is a mesmerizing journey through the boundless realms of ambient, electronic, and psychedelic music. The album's title, which translates to “quark hour” in German, aptly captures the album's sense of timelessness and boundless exploration.
Öbö Ść, the mastermind behind this cosmic odyssey, is a visionary artist who blends analog and digital sounds to create a unique and immersive sonic landscape. Karol Firmanty, Kris Kolorado, and A.J. Kaufmann add their own distinct talents to the mix, weaving intricate guitar textures and cosmic melodies into the fabric of the album.
Kwasarstunde is a must-have for fans of Kosmische Musik, ambient, and psychedelic music. It's an album that will transport you to another dimension and leave you longing for more.
Säure Adler.credits:
released October 31, 2017
Music by Roman Bromboszcz, Adam Majdecki-Janicki.
Artwork by Adam Majdecki-Janicki.
℗ © Via Kosmische
Musicnauts:
Öbö Ść - electronics, direction.
Karol Firmanty - electronics.
Kris Kolorado - guitar.
A.J. Kaufmann - guitar.
Album artwork based on "Visions Of The Future" by C. Foster.

Säure Adler.title: Pilzmusik
Säure Adler.about:
Embark on a transformative sonic journey into the ethereal realm of A.J. Kaufmann's Pilzmusik, an album that seamlessly blends the captivating allure of Kosmische Musik, the meditative ambiance of New Age, and the electrifying intensity of Noise Rock.
The album's title, "Pilzmusik," translates to "mushroom music," a nod to the entheogenic experiences that have profoundly shaped Kaufmann's musical vision. Just as mushrooms can transport consciousness to uncharted realms, Kaufmann's compositions delve into the depths of the psyche, weaving tapestries of sound that oscillate between serenity and intensity.
Whether you're seeking solace and tranquility or an adrenaline-fueled sonic adventure, Pilzmusik has something to offer every discerning listener. It's an album that demands to be experienced, to be immersed in, to be absorbed into the depths of your consciousness.
So, prepare to embark on a transformative sonic odyssey as A.J. Kaufmann guides you through the psychedelic landscapes of Pilzmusik. Let the music wash over you, let it transport you to new realms of consciousness, and let it awaken the cosmic rhythms within your soul.
Säure Adler.credits:
released January 15, 2019
Words and Music by Adam Majdecki-Janicki.
Artwork by Adam Majdecki-Janicki.
℗ © Via Kosmische
Musicnauts:
Adam Majdecki-Janicki - voice, electric and acoustic guitars, bass guitar, synthesizer, organ, flute, drum machine, percussion, tapes.

Säure Adler.title: Signals MMXX
Säure Adler.about:
"Signals MMXX" is inspired mostly by former East German sci-fi cinema, the tracks are imaginary soundtracks to sequences from the movies and to movies not yet unearthed which are certainly waiting for curious seekers.
There also appears the legendary "Solaris" ("Ghosts of Solaris"), and "Planet of the Apes" ("Phase Return to Earth").
Science-fiction rock is the keyword for this brand new 2020 release by Starship Säure Adler.
"Eolomea" is especially dedicated to the memory of Florian Schneider.
Säure Adler.credits:
released November 22, 2020
Music and words by A.J. Kaufmann, 2020.
Recorded at Via Kosmische November 2020.

Säure Adler.title: Zmiana Kosmicznego Adresu
Säure Adler.about:
Prepare to be transported on a mesmerizing musical journey with A.J. Kaufmann's captivating album, "Zmiana Kosmicznego Adresu," a Polish phrase that translates to "Changing Your Cosmic Address." This evocative title encapsulates the album's essence, inviting listeners to embark on a transformative sonic exploration that transcends the boundaries of traditional music genres.
The album title's connection to dub culture lies in its rhythmic elements and atmospheric textures. Dub, a subgenre of reggae, is characterized by its emphasis on bass lines, echo effects, and spatial layering, which resonate deeply in Kaufmann's music. The album's dub-like qualities contribute to its overall meditative and introspective nature, transporting listeners to a realm of sonic bliss.
"Zmiana Kosmicznego Adresu" is a must-listen for fans of experimental music, dub enthusiasts, and anyone seeking a profound and transformative sonic experience. Kaufmann's masterful blend of genres creates an album that is both deeply personal and universally relatable. Embark on this cosmic odyssey and prepare to have your mind and soul expanded.
